title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare SKS Variant
location: South Of KZoo, Michigan, United States
postcontent: I am considering trading off a fairly rare SKS variant for the right trade. Not sure what that would be until I see it. But 1st the disclaimer: Trade value is going to be $800ish. Before you gasp, and say 'WTF"? do some research. Sure it's only an SKS, but this isn't a typical SKS. Navy Arms imported SKS rifles back in the day from Norinco. They configured them for commercial use, targeting hunters, ranch foks etc. They introduced their models accordingly. This one was what they called the "Cowboy Companion". Their target audience was the Ranch owners to use as a Coyote ranch rifle. They shortened them to the Para length, clipped the bayo and filled the bayo slot, mounted a unique scope mount on them and offered them with or without a scope. They also offered an optional 5 round magazine. The 5 round magazine was not a very popular option resulting in a pretty rare option on them these days. This one has that rare 5 round optional magazine. The Scope mount on these are very rare because many took them off and put on a better scope, and tossed the original, resulting in a very rare mount system today. This mount would cost you almost as much as a standard SKS assuming you can even find one. The scope, not "as" rare as the mount, is also a sought collector scope in it's own right. Basically, this mount and scope would cost north of $400 on it's own. The rifle, alone between $400-$500. Finding them together as a correct package is a rarity today. If you do the research, you will find that $800 although nuts, isn't a stretch for a clean, correct, with correct scope and mount Cowboy Companion Navy Arms SKS variant. This is an investment rifle. Now, that said, don't believe what I am typing, go do the research and the math. It is, what it is. ;)
